cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with facial landmark localization using deep learning techniques, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The proposed method involves optimizing the dual-pathway architecture, which can be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also evaluates the performance on multiple face alignment databases, which can be classified under multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses distance-aware soft-max functions, which can be related to neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
